Congratulations to our very own Whitney Ehnert, art teacher extraordinaire at UMS, for being honored with the Middle School Division Award for 2020 by the Art Educators of New Jersey (AENJ).

Ms. Ehnert is a treasure for our students and we are excited to see her receive this well deserved recognition. She not only devotes herself fully to giving our students here in Montgomery an incredible arts education, but she also works hard for kids across the state through her leadership role at the county level for Youth Art Month.

Congratulations Ms. Ehnert!

The students of our middle and high school art programs are proud to present this virtual arts extravaganza. We are so proud of our students' hard work and incredible creativity.

Much of the work in this gallery was created as a part of our distance learning instruction. We invite you to peruse through this gallery of work and hope it brings you joy, makes you think, and adds beauty to your day.

Thank you to the National Art Honor Society at MHS for building this beautiful space for our students' work and thank you to our fantastic art teachers. Enjoy!

post_text: Congratulations to our 2020 National Latin Exam winners. An incredible 83% of our test takers earned an award this year (vs. 38% Nationally). Among the awards were eight gold and twelve silver medal winners. These included Benjamin Meerson, who is in the seventh grade and studying Latin on his own with his dad, and Virankah Peter who earned a Perfect Paper, placing her in the top ½ of one percent of test takers worldwide. Bene factum, omnes! We are incredibly proud of you!
shared_text:
MTSD.K12.NJ.US
World Languages / 2020 National Latin Exam Results
text:
Congratulations to our 2020 National Latin Exam winners. An incredible 83% of our test takers earned an award this year (vs. 38% Nationally). Among the awards were eight gold and twelve silver medal winners. These included Benjamin Meerson, who is in the seventh grade and studying Latin on his own with his dad, and Virankah Peter who earned a Perfect Paper, placing her in the top ½ of one percent of test takers worldwide. Bene factum, omnes! We are incredibly proud of you!

MTSD.K12.NJ.US
World Languages / 2020 National Latin Exam Results

post_text:
The MHS Athletic Dept. is proud to announce our Scholar-Athlete Award Winners for the Class of 2020.

NJSIAA Scholar Athlete: Sarah Witt
Sarah is a member of our Winter and Spring Track teams. She will be attending UMass- Amherst in the fall where she will be running for their Track program.

Skyland Conference Male Scholar Athlete: Carter McFadden
Carter is a member of our Football and Track programs. He will be continuing his academic and football career at Columbia University in the fall.

Skyland Conference Female Scholar Athlete: Ivy Zhao
Ivy is a member of our Cross Country and Track programs. She is currently undecided on her college choice for the fall.

Somerset County Male Scholar Athlete: Kevin O'Brien
Kevin is a member of our Football and Track programs. He will be continuing his academic and football career at Carnegie Mellon University in the fall.

Somerset County Female Scholar Athlete: Emma Noyelle
Emma is a member of our Cross Country and Track programs. She will be attending St. Olaf College in the fall.

Congratulations to all our MHS Scholar Athletes!

post_text:
Congratulations to our MHS Latin students from both Mr. Beyer's and Mr. Dominick's classes for their exceptional performance in the 2019 National Latin Exam.

35 MHS students took the National Latin Exam in March, and 25 earned awards for outstanding performance (71% vs. 38% nationally!). Distinctions include six gold and nine silver medal winners: Andrew Wan, Angela Zhou, Ayanna Jaikishen, Benjamin Meerson, Cailin Howe, Catherine Lin, Christopher Tai, Dara McNally, Elizabeth Laub, Hunter Myers, Jason Li, Joi Myers, Michele Meola, Neena O’Mara, Shuyang He.

Special recognition should be given to Mr. Dominick’s Latin II classes, an incredible 85% of whom earned an award! Bene factum!

The National Latin Exam is offered under the joint sponsorship of the American Classical League and the National Junior Classical League. The exams taken at Montgomery High School this year were Latin I, Latin II, Latin III, and Latin IV Prose. Categories within exams include grammar, comprehension, mythology, life, history, derivatives, and questions based on a short passage in Latin.

Team 1403 competed in the FIRST Mid-Atlantic District Championship on April 4, 5 & 6 at Lehigh University.
The robot and drive team made it into the Semi Final Rounds, no easy feat with 60 of the best teams in NJ, Eastern PA and DE.

The Team was honored with winning the FMA District Chairman's Award, the most prestigious award in FIRST.
Team 1403 will go on to compete at the FIRST Robotics World Competition in Detroit, April 24-27

This award was for all of the outstanding work the team does with their outreach, hosting a competition, teaching and spreading STEM Education in the team, community and globally. Congratulations Team 1403!

Team 1403, Cougar Robotics, is hosting a “Women in STEM” event to encourage young women to join the fields of science, technology, engineering and math. We have brought together an amazing group of passionate women who are educators, researchers, doctors, directors, and company owners.

The event consists on a “Meet and Greet” as well as a panel discussion in which attendees will be able to have one-on-one conversations with all the women and listen to them discuss challenges they have faced as well as what they learned from their career.

Please come and join us on March 31st, 2019: 10:00 am – 11:00 am Meet and Greet and 11:00 am to 12:00 pm Panel Discussion. The event will take place at Montgomery High School, 1016 Co Rd 601, Skillman, NJ 08558 and is open to the public.

Congratulations to the MathCounts State Team consisting of George Cao, Caroline Liu, Prineet Parhar and Jeffrey Xu. This weekend at Rutgers they placed second in the state, which was the highest state ranking Montgomery has received in the last TEN years.

post_text: The data on vaping is staggering. Parents, please educate yourselves on the types of devices and harmful effects. Kids who vape have a significantly higher risk of smoking cigarettes. Yes, the same kids who would never dream of touching a cigarette are the same ones becoming addicted to nicotine.

text:
The data on vaping is staggering. Parents, please educate yourselves on the types of devices and harmful effects. Kids who vape have a significantly higher risk of smoking cigarettes. Yes, the same kids who would never dream of touching a cigarette are the same ones becoming addicted to nicotine.

post_text:
This afternoon, the District held a reunification drill enhancing our school safety and crisis management plans. The purpose of a reunification drill is to bring students and their parents together following an incident when reunification is necessary. We know from many school incidences, returning children to their parents as quickly as reasonably possible is a priority.

We want to thank Mr. Delgado for his leadership and coordination of this important effort and the UMS students and their parents who volunteered to be a part of the drill this afternoon. With your assistance we were able to conduct a “live” relocation and reunification simulation involving students and their parents. The success of this drill would not have been possible without the support and guidance of the Montgomery Police Department, first responders and our District Reunification and Safety Teams. Thank you to all involved.
